description:
Rahway River Race
Hosted by Aleon Cycling Wear and Karma Racing Team
course: COURSE DESCRIPTION:  A mostly flat and fast course around the park. Road pavement is aceptable almost for the entire circuit.  Closed course, so no traffic.  The circuit is approximately 1.1 mile in length, with 2 sharp left hand turns.
registration:
TIME:  Day of starts at 6:00am.  Registration will close 15 minutes prior to each race.
7:00am start for first race.  All other categories are the approximate start times noted above.
notes:
RULES:  All USAC rules apply.  USAC permit pending.
             No free laps except in the 1/2 race and then only prior to 5 laps before the finish.
             No feeding.
             Fields limited to 100 total,  Cat 5 limited to 50.
             Promoter reserves the right to combine fields and shorten races on race day.
             Promoter reserves the right to reduce purse proportionally if field minimums are not met.  
            Photo finish results will be provided.    
           Entry Fee for racers includes a required $4.00 USAC insurance surcharge & $2.00 N.J.B.A. surcharge.  An Additional fee of $10. will be charged for USAC 1 day license.
directions:
From North:  GSP to Exit 135:   There are two lanes that go straight and one that goes right.  Go straight to the second light amd make a left, go under the GSP -( from the right lane), through the traffic light, to the second right towards Linden.  This exit will become Valley Rd.  after the traffic light, stay on Valley Rd.  until the entrance to the Park right after crossing the river.   
From South:  GSP to Exit 135 - CLARK:  exit ramp stay in the center lane, at the light, make a right towards Linden.  This exit will become Valley Rd.  after the traffic light, stay on Valley Rd.  until the entrance to the Park right after crossing the river.    
 
Parking will be permitted in the park before 7am.  After 7am, the police may not let any vehicles into the park.  Arrive early to ensure parking availability.

title: Bridgeton Cross (NJCX)
description:
Bridgeton Cross (NJCX)
Bridgeton, NJ, Sun Sep 24, 2017
course: Bridgeton Cross race course is about 4km long & offers a wide variety of terrain. Hard pack dirt & & fast road sections, paved section, 80 meter beach run, steep "rideable" climbs, dirt run up, and one barrier section. The pit is double sided entry. Racers entering the pit Must make some sort of mechanical adjustment before re-entering the race course. The start line is at the intersection of West Park Drive & Mayor Aitken Drive.
registration:
Race & Registration Info

Your bib number will be pinned on your right side. Your racing age is determined by how old you will be on December 31, 2018. Day of race registration will be available with a "day of" fee of $10.00. Registration opens @7:30 A.M. and closes 30 minutes before the start of each race. A USA Cycling License is needed to race. A One-Day race license will be available for $10.00. No Cat 5 One-Day race licensed riders will be allowed in the Master category events. You must pre-reg to be seeded-get your call up. Call up's are determined by 1. NJBA Garden State Cross Series rankings, 2. in order of pre-reg, 3. bib number. Want to double up & do two races, then we will give you a $10.00 discount on that 2nd race. Race results will be posted at the race reg table and will be finalized 15 minutes after they are posted. Awards, podium will be conducted after race results are finalized at the race reg table. Lapped racers will finish on the same lap as the leaders. Lapped riders must yield to race leaders when being lapped. There is no riding on the course while a race is in progress. Mountain bikes without bar ends are okay to race.
notes:
Disclaimer

The promoter reserves the right to combine categories, change start times, etc

*Cash prizes will be listed or 50% of gate receipts for that category, which ever is less.
directions:
From the Delaware Memorial Bridge, follow signs for Route 49 South. Follow Route 49 into Bridgeton and make a left turn onto Atlantic Street. Drive on Atlantic Street into the City Park and look for the race parking signs.  

From Route 55 South, take Exit 32B for Route 56 West (Landis Ave.). Follow Route 56 West to Route 77. Turn left onto Route 77 South. Follow Route 77 and make a right turn onto Washington Street. Follow Washington & make a right turn onto Mayor Aitken Drive and look for the race parking signs.  

From NJ Turnpike take Exit 2 for Mullica HillRoute 322. Follow Route 322 West into Mullica Hill and make a right turn onto Route 45 South. Follow Route 45 South through Mullica Hill and bear right onto Route 77 South. Follow directions above.

From I-295 take Exit 11 for Route 322. Follow Route 322 West to Mullica Hill. Follow directions above.

title: Westwood Velo Cross Race
description:
The 2017 " Cross for a Cure for Kids " Cyclocross Race

Supporting:  Pediatric Cancer Research Foundation

www.pcrf-kids.org

          SPONSORED BY WESTWOOD VELO 
         (SUNDAY ONLY) November 26, 2017  

 

           

 


     Online Registration Closes Friday, Nov 24, 2017 at 5:00 PM ET.

     DAY OF RACE REGISTRATION (+$10.00) WILL BE ACCEPTED

        PRE-REGISTRATION IS STRONGLY SUGGESTED.

             All start times are approximate, may change as needed.
 

If you are registering for 2 classes, the second class registration fee will be $15. Mountain bikes are ok for all races, no bar ends. Mountain bike license's are ok for all races.

Late fee $10 day of registration does not apply to U19.  Must have valid USAC license to participate. One day license available day of race for $10 additional fee. Must have drivers license, birth certificate or valid passport to purchase. * We reserve the right to combine fields with fewer than fifteen entrants.

* Cash prizes will be as listed or 50% of gate receipts for that category, whichever is less.

 

Let's share the pain and suffering by using: #WestwoodCycle
course:
Course: A 2 Mile loop in the beach area of Wawayand Lake in Wawayanda State Park.  The course has a 

little bit of everything a cross racer is hoping for or dreading:  sand sections, a run up, some short power sections, and 

wooded technical terrain.
